parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Vibration while driving
bubbles or bulges in the tire tread
tire tread separation
damage to surrounding vehicle components (e.g.
quarter panels
tail pipes
shock absorbers).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden detachment of the sunroof panel can cause distraction, injury, or obstruction to the driver's vision, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The sunroof panel falls down or detaches while driving
noise or rattling sound from the sunroof area
obstruction of the driver's view
injury or debris in the passenger compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the braking system can cause loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities, especially when towing a trailer.
symptoms: Sudden loss of braking power
inability to slow down or stop the vehicle
trailer jackknifing or loss of control
unusual noises or vibrations when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the trailer brake system can cause loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities, especially when towing a trailer.
symptoms: Sudden loss of braking power
inability to slow down or stop the trailer
trailer jackknifing or loss of control
unusual noises or vibrations when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty seat belt system can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident, as occupants may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: The seat belt will not latch or unlatch
the seat belt is stuck
the seat belt warning light is illuminated
the seat belt pretensioner is not functioning
the seat belt is not retracting properly.
